---

<section id="about" class="py-16 sm:py-24 bg-white">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 lg:gap-16 items-center">
      <!-- Photo placeholder -->
      <div class="relative">
        <div class="rounded-2xl overflow-hidden bg-neutral-100 aspect-[4/5] flex items-center justify-center border border-neutral-200/60">
          <div class="text-center p-8">
            <div class="w-14 h-14 mx-auto mb-3 rounded-xl bg-neutral-200/60 flex items-center justify-center">
              <svg class="w-7 h-7 text-neutral-400" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M15.75 6a3.75 3.75 0 11-7.5 0 3.75 3.75 0 017.5 0zM4.501 20.118a7.5 7.5 0 0114.998 0A17.933 17.933 0 0112 21.75c-2.676 0-5.216-.584-7.499-1.632z" />
              </svg>
            </div>
            <p class="text-neutral-500 font-medium text-sm">Add a photo of Anesh with a dog</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="absolute -bottom-4 right-4 sm:right-8 bg-white rounded-xl shadow-lg p-4 border border-neutral-100">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-k9-green/10 flex items-center justify-center">
              <span class="text-k9-green font-bold text-sm">10+</span>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-bold text-neutral-900 text-sm">Years experience</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-neutral-400">Since 2011</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p class="text-k9-green font-semibold text-sm tracking-wide uppercase mb-3">Meet Anesh</p>
        <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-extrabold text-neutral-900 mb-6">
          I respond to every inquiry personally. Here's why.
        </h2>

        <div class="space-y-4 text-neutral-500 leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            Most trainers won't tell you this: the biggest reason dogs fail training is because the trainer doesn't understand the dog in front of them. They use cookie-cutter methods and hope something sticks.
          </p>
          <p>
            I've been training dogs since 2011. I've worked with the breeds most trainers refuse — malinois, GSDs, huskies, the dogs with bite histories, the ones other trainers called "too far gone."
          </p>
          <p>
            I built K9 Academy because I saw too many dogs and owners get failed by trainers who wouldn't use the right tools. We use balanced training — including e-collar protocols — because the results speak for themselves.
          </p>
          <p class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">
            When you reach out, you talk to me. Not a receptionist. Not a chatbot. Me.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-8 flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4">
          <a
            href="#contact"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-6 py-3 bg-neutral-900 text-white text-sm font-semibold rounded-xl hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-all"
          >
            Talk to Anesh
          </a>
          <a
            href="tel:4377785273"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 text-neutral-600 text-sm font-semibold rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 hover:border-neutral-300 hover:bg-neutral-50 transition-all"
          >
            <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M2.25 6.75c0 8.284 6.716 15 15 15h2.25a2.25 2.25 0 002.25-2.25v-1.372c0-.516-.351-.966-.852-1.091l-4.423-1.106c-.44-.11-.902.055-1.173.417l-.97 1.293c-.282.376-.769.542-1.21.38a12.035 12.035 0 01-7.143-7.143c-.162-.441.004-.928.38-1.21l1.293-.97c.363-.271.527-.734.417-1.173L6.963 3.102a1.125 1.125 0 00-1.091-.852H4.5A2.25 2.25 0 002.25 4.5v2.25z" />
            </svg>
            437-778-5273
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
